SECTION 1. Sections one, two, two-A and two-B of Republic Act Numbered Three thousand seven hundred eighty-three, as amended and/or inserted by Republic Act

Numbered Four thousand one hundred and forty, are hereby repealed and in lieu thereof the following sections are enacted:

"SECTION 1. The state prosecutors and the prosecuting and other attorneys in the Prosecution Division and Deportation Board, as provided by existing laws, are hereby merged into one prosecution service which shall be known as the Prosecution Staff of the Department of Justice. The said staff, as enlarged by this Act, shall have one chief, to be known as Chief State Prosecutor, three Assistant Chief State Prosecutors, and the following:

"(a) Six senior state prosecutors, each of whom shall receive an annual salary of P800.00 less than that herein provided for the Assistant Chief State Prosecutor;

"(b) Sis senior state prosecutors, each at P600.00 less than that provided for in the next preceding paragraph;

"(c) Six state prosecutors, each at P600.00 less than that provided for in the next preceding paragraph;

