"(f) Ten state prosecutors, each at T600.00 less than that provided for in the next preceding paragraph;

"(g) Ten state prosecutors, each at P600.00 less than that provided for in the next preceding paragraph;

"(h) Sixteen district state prosecutors, each at P600.00 less than that provided for in

the next preceding paragraph; and

"(i) Two prosecuting attorneys, each at Pl,200.00 less than that provided for in the next preceding paragraph.

"SEC. 2. The Chief State Prosecutor, the Assistant Chief State Prosecutors, the Senior State Prosecutors, the State Prosecutors, and the District State Prosecutors shall be appointed by the President of the Philippines with the consent of the Commission on Appointments:

Provided,

Provided,

That said prosecutors shall only assist or collaborate with the provincial or city fiscal, unless otherwise expressly directed and authorized by the Secretary of Justice.

"The Chief State Prosecutor, the Assistant Chief State Prosecutors, the Senior State Prosecutors, and the State Prosecutors shall also prosecute deportation cases, investigate administrative charges against fiscals, and perform such other duties as may be assigned to them by the Secretary of Justice in the interest of the public Service.

